 LINUS CHIBUIKE A Special Investigation Task Force set up by the Inspector-General of Police, Mohammed Adamu, has arrived Makurdi, in Benue State. The Task Force was set up to fish out those behind the recent attack and attempted murder of Governor Samuel Ortom of Benue State. The Team, led by DCP Abba Kyari, a no-nonsense investigator, comprises operatives from the Tactical Investigation Units of the Force Intelligence Bureau and other experienced, crack detectives with specialised competencies in crime scene investigation and reconstruction, ballistics, fingerprint analysis and other core areas of forensics. Force Public Relations Officer, CP Frank Mba, disclosed this in a statement. He said the team was expected to take over and consolidate all ongoing investigation into the attempted murder incident. Mba said the Team was also expected to investigate all angles of the reported attack with a view to ensuring that all persons empirically linked to the incident were apprehended and brought to book. “Meanwhile, the Inspector-General of Police has charged the team to be professional, thorough and clinical in their investigations,” he said. “They are expected to liaise and work with the Benue State Police Command and other relevant members of the law enforcement community to ensure that they deliver on their mandate,” Mba added. 